On the afternoon of Monday, September 26, 2022, Drs Tzanki Doukov and Blaine Mooers co-chaired a four-hour workshop for the third year in a row.
It had eight speakers from three continents.

The topics were quite divserse: micro-ED, cryo-EM, SAXS, radiation damage analysis, solvent channel analsysis, and direct phasing. 
All of the talks were reviting. 
However, the last speaker really hit a home-run with some very exciting results about extending direct phasing methods.
The talk was mentioned several times in other workshops on the following days.
